{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17514734","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17514734"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:25:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:25:55+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12370"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12370","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12370"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.08,0.2,0.02,0.68,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4884"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77817"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4884"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12370"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63338"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1109"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"3343"},{"type":"tags","id":"3764"},{"type":"tags","id":"3804"},{"type":"tags","id":"4847"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"12912"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"7917"},{"type":"contributions","id":"7925"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26726"},{"type":"contributions","id":"35737"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42747"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43322"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44792"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/77817"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 80-year-old man presents to the Emergency Department with a one-week history of generalised weakness, bone pain, constipation, increasing drowsiness, and confusion. He has recently been diagnosed with metastatic non-small cell lung cancer. He has had no recent falls. On examination, he is disoriented to time, place, and person. His blood pressure is 120/70 mmHg, pulse 98/min, temperature 37.0\u00b0C, respiratory rate 14/min, and SpO2 92% on room air. There are no focal neurological deficits, and his pupils are equal and reactive to light, with no papilloedema. The right hemithorax is dull to percussion with reduced breath sounds. The rest of the examination is normal.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following investigations will be of the most value in the immediate management?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Complete blood examination","Serum electrolytes","Liver function tests","Serum calcium and phosphate","Blood cultures"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with symptoms suggestive of hypercalcaemia, such as confusion, constipation, and bone pain, in the context of metastatic non-small cell lung cancer. Hypercalcaemia in malignancy often results from osteolytic metastases or paraneoplastic syndromes, where the tumour secretes parathyroid hormone-related peptide, leading to increased bone resorption and renal tubular reabsorption of calcium.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum calcium and phosphate\u003C/strong\u003E levels are crucial in diagnosing hypercalcaemia of malignancy, which is an oncological emergency requiring prompt management to prevent complications like arrhythmias. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EComplete blood examination\u003C/strong\u003E could reveal anaemia or infection, but these are not immediately life-threatening compared to hypercalcaemia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESerum electrolytes\u003C/strong\u003E might show hyponatraemia, possibly due to SIADH, but this is less likely to cause the acute symptoms described.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver function tests\u003C/strong\u003E could indicate liver metastases or hepatic encephalopathy, but the clinical presentation does not strongly suggest these conditions.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlood cultures\u003C/strong\u003E would be relevant if sepsis were suspected, but the absence of fever or infection signs makes this less likely.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Hypercalcaemia should be considered in patients with metastatic cancer presenting with confusion and other systemic symptoms.","Serum calcium and phosphate levels are crucial in diagnosing hypercalcaemia of malignancy.","Hypercalcaemia is an oncological emergency requiring prompt management."],"references":["Bergman PJ. Paraneoplastic hypercalcemia. Top Companion Anim Med. 2012 Nov;27(4):156-8. doi: 10.1053/j.tcam.2012.09.003. PMID: 23415382. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23415382/","Chong WH, Molinolo AA, Chen CC, Collins MT. Tumor-induced osteomalacia. Endocr Relat Cancer. 2011 Jun 8;18(3):R53-77. doi: 10.1530/ERC-11-0006. PMID: 21490240; PMCID: PMC3433741. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/21490240/","Fritchie K, Zedek D, Grenache DG. The clinical utility of parathyroid hormone-related peptide in the assessment of hypercalcemia. Clin Chim Acta. 2009 Apr;402(1-2):146-9. doi: 10.1016/j.cca.2008.12.040. Epub 2009 Jan 11. PMID: 19168044. Avaialble from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19168044/","Iyer P, Ibrahim M, Siddiqui W, Dirweesh A. Syndrome of inappropriate secretion of anti-diuretic hormone (SIADH) as an initial presenting sign of non small cell lung cancer-case report and literature review. Respir Med Case Rep. 2017 Aug 11;22:164-167. doi: 10.1016/j.rmcr.2017.08.004. PMID: 28856088; PMCID: PMC5565784. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC5565784/","Rigante M, Loperfido A, Paludetti G. Oncogenic Osteomalacia with Elevated Fibroblast Growth Factor 23: A Rare Case of Paranasal Sinus Tumor Onset. Cureus. 2019 Jun 17;11(6):e4919. doi: 10.7759/cureus.4919. PMID: 31423395; PMCID: PMC6692094. Available from: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31423395/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63338"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12370"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63338","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/63338"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-08T12:44:51+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-08T12:45:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4884"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"77817"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemC